cs.CR, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.NI, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a program logic for verifying the security guarantees of secure inter-domain routing protocols. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the development of a sound program logic for a declarative specification language. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of a verification condition generator and a compiler for SANDLog. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper focuses on secure routing protocols. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also relevant as the paper discusses the implementation and empirical evaluation of secure routing protocols.
